##### [B.2.6.2.](#appendix-B.2.6.2) [Invocation via the Digital Credentials API](#name-invocation-via-the-digital-)

If the presentation request is invoked using the Digital Credentials API, the `SessionTranscript` CBOR structure as defined in Section 9.1.5.1 in \[[ISO.18013-5](#ISO.18013-5)\] MUST be used with the following changes:[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-1)

*   `DeviceEngagementBytes` MUST be `null`.[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-2.1)
*   `EReaderKeyBytes` MUST be `null`.[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-2.2)
*   `Handover` MUST be the `OpenID4VPDCAPIHandover` CBOR structure as defined below.[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-2.3)

Note: The following section contains a definition in Concise Data Definition Language (CDDL), a language used to define data structures - see \[[RFC8610](#RFC8610)\] for more details. `bstr` refers to Byte String, defined as major type 2 in CBOR and `tstr` refers to Text String, defined as major type 3 in CBOR (encoded in utf-8) as defined in section 3.1 of \[[RFC8949](#RFC8949)\].[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-3)

```
OpenID4VPDCAPIHandover = [
  "OpenID4VPDCAPIHandover", ; A fixed identifier for this handover type
  OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfoHash ; A cryptographic hash of OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfo
]

; Contains the sha-256 hash of OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfoBytes
OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfoHash = bstr

; Contains the bytes of OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfo encoded as CBOR
OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfoBytes = bstr .cbor OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfo

OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfo = [
  origin,
  nonce,
  jwkThumbprint
] ; Array containing handover parameters

origin = tstr

nonce = tstr

jwkThumbprint = bstr

```


[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-4)

The `OpenID4VPDCAPIHandover` structure has the following elements:[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-5)

*   The first element MUST be the string `OpenID4VPDCAPIHandover`. This serves as a unique identifier for the handover structure to prevent misinterpretation or confusion.[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-6.1)
*   The second element MUST be a Byte String which contains the sha-256 hash of the bytes of `OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfo` when encoded as CBOR.[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-6.2)
*   The `OpenID4VPDCAPIHandoverInfo` has the following elements:[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-6.3.1)
    
    *   The first element MUST be the string representing the Origin of the request as described in [Appendix A.2](#dc_api_request). It MUST NOT be prefixed with `origin:`.[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-6.3.2.1)
    *   The second element MUST be the value of the `nonce` request parameter.[¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-6.3.2.2)
    *   For the Response Mode `dc_api.jwt`, the third element MUST be the JWK SHA-256 Thumbprint as defined in \[[RFC7638](#RFC7638)\], encoded as a Byte String, of the Verifier's public key used to encrypt the response. If the Response Mode is `dc_api`, the third element MUST be `null`. For unsigned requests, including the JWK Thumbprint in the `SessionTranscript` allows the Verifier to detect whether the response was re-encrypted by a third party, potentially leading to the leakage of sensitive information. While this does not prevent such an attack, it makes it detectable and helps preserve the confidentiality of the response.  
        [¶](#appendix-B.2.6.2-6.3.2.3)

